<br>
<br>
Malachaii Elfkiller <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=collainmacbain>Collain MacBain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/12/02 10:25:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3527.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well well well...</span><hr size=1> I agree that it is harsh and also very late, but at the same time I cannot see what else they could have done.<br>
<br>
With the population of smite clerics skyrocketing due to the perceived 'uberness' of the class and the fact that a single smite cleric could take out 2-3 similar con opponents, they had do something to weaken the class.<br>
<br>
If the current number of a 22% reduction is found to be correct I cannot see how this is such a catastrophic nerf. A smite cleric will still be a formidable opponent for my shade. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/utreadlightly.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Treadlightly</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/12/02 10:40:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3527.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It offical, Clerics nerfed...</span><hr size=1> <br>
This nerf will be very well received by people in Albion (with the exception of clerics...lol).  Unless you play in Albion, you wouldn't beleive how much people hate smite clerics.  Often people would rant like crazy and drum a cleric out of a group because they thought the cleric got into the group under the pretense of being a healer even though they were heavily spec'd in smite.  Personally, this never bothered me, I'd always ask a cleric how they spec'd so I would know what to expect.  <br>
<br>
Still, I kinda like this &quot;nerf&quot; for two reasons.  First, I think smite did make clerics a bit overpowered.  Although there is no way they nuked like wizzies or other traditional nukers, a cleric could nonetheless be very powerful if they spec'd heavily in smite.  Second and most importantly, because the &quot;Smite Cleric&quot; template is so appealing to many players, Albion is filled with clerics who can't heal very well.  Hopefully, this nerf will make many of them respec to rejuv/enhance so it will be easier to find a good healer/buffer.  <br>
<br>
And, if it does, Albion's RvR ability will benefit a great deal.  So many smite clerics fancy themselves damage dealers who are invincible because of chain, insta-heal, etc.  They are usually on the front lines trying to get kills or often going off to solo.   As a result they dont act as healers and ignore everyone's &quot;/y need a heal!&quot;   In my experience, the mid or hib I am beating on gets healed in combat by his realm's healers much more often then we Albs do from our clerics.  <br>
<br>
All in all I think that this nerf is probably bad news for mids and hibs.  Increasing the number of good healers on the battlefield who support the fighters around them will increase Albion's RvR capability far more then the loss of some mediocre nuking ability will hurt it. <br>
